{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund new Jewish community centres to foster cohesion and combat antisemitism.",
        "additional_details": "Following attacks/vandalism, current funding focuses on security. We seek investment in new, diverse centres outside traditional areas for growing populations. Funding must enable resilience and the celebration of life, not just defence. Hubs will host vital interfaith/public education, actively breaking down barriers and showing Jewish life is welcome, valued, and protected.",
        "background": "We urge the Government to create a dedicated funding stream, administered by the Home Office or DLUHC, to support the construction and refurbishment of Jewish community centres and synagogues in areas with growing Jewish populations.",
